name: ListQueue
comment:
List based dart-collection.Queue.

Keeps a cyclic buffer of elements, and grows to a larger buffer when it fills up. This guarantees constant time peek and remove operations, and amortized constant time add operations.

The structure is efficient for any queue or stack usage.

iterator.name: iterator
iterator.comment: Returns an Iterator that iterates over this Iterable object.

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no element in this collection.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of elements in this.

Counting all elements may be involve running through all elements and can therefore be slow.

first.name: first
first.comment:
Returns the first element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError. Otherwise this method is equivalent to this.elementAt(0)

last.name: last
last.comment:
Returns the last element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError.

single.name: single
single.comment:
Returns the single element in this.

If this is empty or has more than one element throws a dart-core.StateError.

constructors.comment:
Create an empty queue.

If dart-collection.ListQueue.ListQueue-.initialCapacity is given, prepare the queue for at least that many elements.

from.name: from
from.comment: Create a queue initially containing the elements of dart-collection.ListQueue.ListQueue-from.source.

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment: Applies the function f to each element of this collection.

elementAt.name: elementAt
elementAt.comment:
Returns the dart-collection.ListQueue.elementAt.indexth element.

The dart-collection.ListQueue.elementAt.index must be non-negative and less than dart-collection.ListQueue.length.

Note: if this does not have a deterministic iteration order then the function may simply return any element without any iteration if there are at least dart-collection.ListQueue.elementAt.index elements in this.

toList.name: toList
toList.comment:
Creates a dart-core.List containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

The elements are in iteration order. The list is fixed-length if dart-collection.ListQueue.toList.growable is false.

add.name: add
add.comment: Adds value at the end of the queue.

addAll.name: addAll
addAll.comment: Adds all elements of iterable at the end of the queue. The length of the queue is extended by the length of iterable.

remove.name: remove
remove.comment:
Remove a single instance of value from the queue.

Returns true if a value was removed, or false if the queue contained no element equal to value.

removeWhere.name: removeWhere
removeWhere.comment:
Remove all elements matched by dart-collection.ListQueue.removeWhere.test.

This method is inefficient since it works by repeatedly removing single elements, each of which can take linear time.

retainWhere.name: retainWhere
retainWhere.comment:
Remove all elements not matched by dart-collection.ListQueue.retainWhere.test.

This method is inefficient since it works by repeatedly removing single elements, each of which can take linear time.

clear.name: clear
clear.comment: Removes all elements in the queue. The size of the queue becomes zero.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

addLast.name: addLast
addLast.comment: Adds value at the end of the queue.

addFirst.name: addFirst
addFirst.comment: Adds value at the beginning of the queue.

removeFirst.name: removeFirst
removeFirst.comment: Removes and returns the first element of this queue. Throws an dart-core.StateError exception if this queue is empty.

removeLast.name: removeLast
removeLast.comment: Removes and returns the last element of the queue. Throws an dart-core.StateError exception if this queue is empty.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides dart-collection.ListQueue.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

iterator.comment: Returns an Iterator that iterates over this Iterable object.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of elements in this.

Counting all elements may be involve running through all elements and can therefore be slow.

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no element in this collection.

isNotEmpty.name: isNotEmpty
isNotEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is at least one element in this collection.

first.name: first
first.comment:
Returns the first element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError. Otherwise this method is equivalent to this.elementAt(0)

last.name: last

Returns the last element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError.

single.name: single
single.comment:
Returns the single element in this.

If this is empty or has more than one element throws a dart-core.StateError.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and dart-collection.ListQueue.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the dart-collection.ListQueue.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
dart-collection.ListQueue.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to dart-collection.ListQueue.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If dart-collection.ListQueue.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of dart-collection.ListQueue.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

map.name: map
map.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable where each element e of this is replaced by the result of f(e).

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function dart-collection.ListQueue.map.f will not be invoked. The transformed elements will not be cached. Iterating multiple times over the the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function dart-collection.ListQueue.map.f multiple times on the same element.

where.name: where
where.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable with all elements that satisfy the predicate dart-collection.ListQueue.where.test.

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function dart-collection.ListQueue.where.test will not be invoked. Iterating will not cache results, and thus iterating multiple times over the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function dart-collection.ListQueue.where.test multiple times on the same element.

expand.name: expand
expand.comment:
Expands each element of this dart-core.Iterable into zero or more elements.

The resulting Iterable runs through the elements returned by dart-collection.ListQueue.expand.f for each element of this, in order.

The returned dart-core.Iterable is lazy, and calls dart-collection.ListQueue.expand.f for each element of this every time it's iterated.

contains.name: contains
contains.comment: Returns true if the collection contains an element equal to dart-collection.ListQueue.contains.element.

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment: Applies the function dart-collection.ListQueue.forEach.f to each element of this collection.

reduce.name: reduce
reduce.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining elements of the collection using the provided function.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.reduce((value, element) => value + element);

fold.name: fold
fold.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining each element of the collection with an existing value using the provided function.

Use dart-collection.ListQueue.fold.initialValue as the initial value, and the function dart-collection.ListQueue.fold.combine to create a new value from the previous one and an element.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.fold(0, (prev, element) => prev + element);

every.name: every
every.comment: Returns true if every elements of this collection satisify the predicate dart-collection.ListQueue.every.test. Returns false otherwise.

join.name: join
join.comment:
Converts each element to a dart-core.String and concatenates the strings.

Converts each element to a dart-core.String by calling dart-collection.ListQueue.toString on it. Then concatenates the strings, optionally separated by the dart-collection.ListQueue.join.separator string.

any.name: any
any.comment: Returns true if one element of this collection satisfies the predicate dart-collection.ListQueue.any.test. Returns false otherwise.

toList.name: toList
toList.comment:
Creates a dart-core.List containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

The elements are in iteration order. The list is fixed-length if dart-collection.ListQueue.toList.growable is false.

toSet.name: toSet
toSet.comment: Creates a dart-core.Set containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

take.name: take
take.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable with at most dart-collection.ListQueue.take.n elements.

The returned dart-core.Iterable may contain fewer than dart-collection.ListQueue.take.n elements, if this contains fewer than dart-collection.ListQueue.take.n elements.

It is an error if dart-collection.ListQueue.take.n is negative.

takeWhile.name: takeWhile
takeWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that stops once dart-collection.ListQueue.takeWhile.test is not satisfied anymore.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable starts iterating over the elements of this.

When the iterator encounters an element e that does not satisfy dart-collection.ListQueue.takeWhile.test, it discards e and moves into the finished state. That is, it does not get or provide any more elements.

skip.name: skip
skip.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips the first dart-collection.ListQueue.skip.n elements.

If this has fewer than dart-collection.ListQueue.skip.n elements, then the resulting Iterable is empty.

It is an error if dart-collection.ListQueue.skip.n is negative.

skipWhile.name: skipWhile
skipWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips elements while dart-collection.ListQueue.skipWhile.test is satisfied.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable iterates over all elements of this.

As long as the iterator's elements satisfy dart-collection.ListQueue.skipWhile.test they are discarded. Once an element does not satisfy the dart-collection.ListQueue.skipWhile.test the iterator stops testing and uses every later element unconditionally. That is, the elements of the returned Iterable are the elements of this starting from the first element that does not satisfy dart-collection.ListQueue.skipWhile.test.

firstWhere.name: firstWhere
firstWhere.comment:
Returns the first element that satisfies the given predicate dart-collection.ListQueue.firstWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the dart-collection.ListQueue.firstWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when dart-collection.ListQueue.firstWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

lastWhere.name: lastWhere
lastWhere.comment:
Returns the last element that satisfies the given predicate dart-collection.ListQueue.lastWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the dart-collection.ListQueue.lastWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when dart-collection.ListQueue.lastWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

singleWhere.name: singleWhere
singleWhere.comment: Returns the single element that satisfies dart-collection.ListQueue.singleWhere.test. If no or more than one element match then a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

elementAt.name: elementAt
elementAt.comment:
Returns the dart-collection.ListQueue.elementAt.indexth element.

The dart-collection.ListQueue.elementAt.index must be non-negative and less than dart-collection.ListQueue.length.

Note: if this does not have a deterministic iteration order then the function may simply return any element without any iteration if there are at least dart-collection.ListQueue.elementAt.index elements in this.

removeFirst.name: removeFirst
removeFirst.comment: Removes and returns the first element of this queue. Throws an dart-core.StateError exception if this queue is empty.

removeLast.name: removeLast
removeLast.comment: Removes and returns the last element of the queue. Throws an dart-core.StateError exception if this queue is empty.

addFirst.name: addFirst
addFirst.comment: Adds dart-collection.ListQueue.addFirst.value at the beginning of the queue.

addLast.name: addLast
addLast.comment: Adds dart-collection.ListQueue.addLast.value at the end of the queue.

add.name: add
add.comment: Adds dart-collection.ListQueue.add.value at the end of the queue.

remove.name: remove
remove.comment:
Remove a single instance of value from the queue.

Returns true if a value was removed, or false if the queue contained no element equal to value.

addAll.name: addAll
addAll.comment: Adds all elements of dart-collection.ListQueue.addAll.iterable at the end of the queue. The length of the queue is extended by the length of dart-collection.ListQueue.addAll.iterable.

removeWhere.name: removeWhere
removeWhere.comment:
Removes all elements matched by dart-collection.ListQueue.removeWhere.test from the queue.

The test function must not throw or modify the queue.

retainWhere.name: retainWhere
retainWhere.comment:
Removes all elements not matched by dart-collection.ListQueue.retainWhere.test from the queue.

The test function must not throw or modify the queue.

clear.name: clear
clear.comment: Removes all elements in the queue. The size of the queue becomes zero.
